Okay, I’ve been staring at this for way too long and my rubber duck has given up on me. I’m making a little pixel-art platformer in JavaScript for fun, and my collision detection is being weird. Sometimes the player just falls straight through the platform like it’s a ghost. Here’s the part of the code that handles it:

```js
if (player.y + player.height >= platform.y &&
    player.y <= platform.y + platform.height &&
    player.x + player.width >= platform.x &&
    player.x <= platform.x + platform.width) {
  player.onGround = true;
} else {
  player.onGround = false;
}
```

Any idea what I’m doing wrong, or should I just accept that gravity hates me personally?
